</ext_description><!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Issue_arm  Entity: Issue  
   <express_ref linkend="issue:arm:Issue_arm.Issue"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Issue_arm.Issue">
        A <b>Issue</b> is a type of
        <express_ref linkend="Observation:arm:Observation_arm.Observation"/>. An <b>Issue</b> has the additional implication that the appropriate issue management authority is expected to act on the issue to resolve it.
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Issue_arm  Entity: Issue_consequence  
   <express_ref linkend="issue:arm:Issue_arm.Issue_consequence"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Issue_arm.Issue_consequence">
        A <b>Issue_consequence</b> is a type of
        <express_ref linkend="Observation:arm:Observation_arm.Observation_consequence"/> which links an issue to the request to resolve the issue.
	</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Issue_arm  Entity: Issue_reference  
   <express_ref linkend="issue:arm:Issue_arm.Issue_reference"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Issue_arm.Issue_reference">
        A <b>Issue_reference</b> is a type of
        <express_ref linkend="Observation:arm:Observation_arm.Observation_assignment" /> that explicitly identifies one or more items that are related to the issue. In general, the attributes of <express_ref linkend="Observation:arm:Observation_arm.Observation_assignment" /> are not used, unless the issue refers to an item outside the scope of the select.
</ext_description>
